  "local_port": 56692,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best plan for international calling in India for people in UAE?",
  "response": "Choosing the best international calling plan from the UAE to India depends on your specific needs, such as the frequency of calls, preferred billing method (prepaid or postpaid), and whether you prefer traditional voice calls or are open to using internet-based services. Below are some of the top options from major UAE telecom providers as of October 2023:\n\n### **1. Etisalat**\n\n**International Calling Add-ons:**\n- **International Call Packs:** Etisalat offers various international add-ons that provide discounted rates for calls to India. These packs can include a certain number of minutes per day or month at reduced rates.\n- **Saudi Calling Add-on:** While primarily for Saudi Arabia, Etisalat also offers similar add-ons for other countries, including India.\n- **Monthly Plans:** Some postpaid plans come with built-in international minutes that can be used specifically for India.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Reliable network coverage and call quality.\n- Flexible options to choose based on your calling frequency.\n\n**How to Subscribe:**\n- You can subscribe via the Etisalat app, website, or by visiting an Etisalat store.\n\n### **2. Du**\n\n**International Calling Packages:**\n- **International Share Plan:** Du offers Share plans that include a bundle of local, international, and SMS minutes, which can be tailored to include a significant portion for India.\n- **Specific Country Bundles:** Du provides country-specific add-ons that offer discounted calling rates to India.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Competitive pricing for international calls.\n- Easy customization of plans based on usage.\n\n**How to Subscribe:**\n- Available through the Du app, website, or at Du retail outlets.\n\n### **3. Virgin Mobile UAE**\n\n**International Roaming and Calling:**\n- **International Add-ons:** Virgin Mobile offers add-ons that include discounted rates for international calls, including India.\n- **Flexible Plans:** Their plans are known for flexibility, allowing you to adjust based on your needs each month.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- User-friendly app for managing your plan and add-ons.\n- No long-term contracts, offering more flexibility.\n\n**How to Subscribe:**\n- Manage and purchase add-ons via the Virgin Mobile app or website.\n\n### **4. VoIP and Internet-Based Services**\n\nIf you're open to using internet-based calling, these can be cost-effective alternatives:\n\n- **Skype, WhatsApp, Viber, and FaceTime:** These apps allow voice and video calls over the internet, often for free or at very low costs.\n- **Rebtel:** Offers affordable international calling rates without the need for an internet connection.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Lower or no cost for calls, depending on the service and your internet connection.\n- Additional features like video calls, messaging, and more.\n\n**Considerations:**\n- Requires a stable internet connection.\n- May not be ideal if you prefer traditional voice calls without using data.\n\n### **5. Comparing Plans**\n\nTo determine the best plan for your needs:\n\n1. **Assess Your Usage:** Determine how many minutes you typically call India each month.\n2. **Compare Rates:** Look at the per-minute rates and bundled minutes offered by Etisalat, Du, and Virgin Mobile.\n3. **Check for Additional Benefits:** Some plans may offer perks like free SMS to India, higher data allowances, or international roaming benefits.\n4. **Customer Support and Reliability:** Consider the reputation of the provider in terms of network reliability and customer service.\n\n### **Recommendation**\n\nFor frequent callers to India, **Etisalat's International Call Packs** and **Du\u2019s International Share Plans** are generally the most cost-effective and reliable options. They offer competitive per-minute rates and flexible bundling options that can be tailored to your specific needs. \n\nHowever, if you prefer flexibility without long-term commitments, **Virgin Mobile UAE** offers attractive pay-as-you-go options that can be adjusted monthly. Additionally, leveraging **VoIP services** can significantly reduce costs if you have access to a good internet connection.\n\n**Always check the latest offers** on the respective provider\u2019s websites or contact their customer service to get the most accurate and up-to-date information tailored to your specific situation.",
